main event: A report from Project Blue Book documented a sighting of a red-grayish-white object in Storm Lake, Iowa on October 10, 1955.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for 1 hour and 4 minutes,The observer was a college student,The object was observed visually from the ground,The possible explanations for the sighting included it being a balloon or an astronomical object,The exact positional data of the object was not provided.
